@startuml 11-swimlane-hiring-to-evaluation
' CVerify — End-to-end swimlane: hiring requirement -> artifacts -> vacancy -> discovery -> matching -> evaluation.
' Verified against:
'   Modules/Shared/System/Controllers/HiringRequirementController.cs
'       create:74 · generate-artifacts:166-204 (detached Task.Run:184) · artifacts:206
'       candidate-matches:375 · discover:392 · publish:440 · progress-stream:466
'   Modules/Shared/System/Services/HiringRequirementService.cs
'       GenerateArtifactsAsync:564-736 (AI path "/api/v1/hiring-requirements/generate/stream":627,
'           HMAC:635-640, SSE loop:644-718, SaveArtifactAsync:711)
'       PublishAsync:271-405 (RequirementSnapshot + ArtifactSnapshots:374-404)
'   Modules/Shared/System/Controllers/JobVacancyController.cs
'       GET requirement vacancy:42 · create-draft:120 · update posting:241 · publish:288
'   Modules/Profiles/Services/CandidateMatchService.cs
'       TriggerDiscoveryAsync:232-289 · ExecuteDiscoveryPipelineAsync:291-392
'       GetCandidateMatchesAsync:57-208 (engine call:180)
'   Modules/Intelligence/Services/ExplainableMatchService.cs:34-145
'   Modules/Intelligence/Services/UnifiedMatchingEngine.cs:206-216
'   Modules/Intelligence/Services/CandidateEvaluationService.cs:44, :509-521
'   Modules/Intelligence/BackgroundWorkers/CandidateRankingProjectionWorker.cs (15 min)
'   Modules/Shared/System/Services/HmacSignatureService.cs
'   CVerify.AI/app/api/routes/analysis_router.py:317
'   CVerify.AI/app/pipelines/requirement/orchestrator.py:45-190
' Ground truth: GROUND-TRUTH.md §2 (roles), §5.3 (HMAC), §5.4 (workers), §6.2 (Line 4), §6.4 (Claude).

title CVerify — Hiring Requirement to Candidate Evaluation (end to end)

|Organization Member|
start
:draft a hiring requirement
(HR / REPRESENTATIVE / OWNER — there is no "Recruiter" role);

|Next.js Client|
:POST /api/v1/hiring-requirements
(axios, HttpOnly cookies + X-CSRF-Token);

|Core API|
:authorize imperatively —
_authService.AuthorizeAsync(userId, orgId,
"permission:name:SCOPETYPE:scopeId");
note right
  An ORGANIZATION-scoped grant implicitly covers child WORKSPACE
  scopes (PermissionEvaluator.cs:95,111). This is one of three
  coexisting authorization mechanisms in the codebase.
end note

|PostgreSQL|
:INSERT HiringRequirement + capabilities
(Status = Draft);

|Organization Member|
:"Generate artifacts";

|Next.js Client|
:POST /api/v1/hiring-requirements/{id}/generate-artifacts;
:open GET /api/v1/hiring-requirements/{id}/progress-stream (SSE);

|Core API|
:202 Accepted { jobId = id, status = "Generating" };
:spawn a **detached Task.Run** with its own DI scope
and CancellationToken.None;
note right #ffdddd
  Artifact generation is not queued and not hosted by an
  IHostedService — nothing recovers it across a restart.
  Contrast the repository pipeline, which at least has
  AnalysisQueueRecoverySweeper.
end note

|Background Worker|
:status -> Generating; create AiStreamingSession
("jd-generation", "Claude 3.5 Sonnet");
:HmacSignatureService.CreateSignatureHeaders
HMACSHA256(METHOD + URL + BODY + TIMESTAMP + NONCE, SharedSecret);
:POST /api/v1/hiring-requirements/generate/stream
X-Client-Id, X-Timestamp, X-Nonce,
X-Correlation-Id, X-Signature;

|AI Service|
:verify_hmac_signature;
:build the unified requirements prompt;

|Anthropic Claude|
:one streaming completion
(stream=True, max_tokens=8192,
cache_control: ephemeral);

|AI Service|
:_repair_and_extract_json (json_repair fallback);
if (UnifiedRequirementArtifactsResponse validates?) then (no)
  :re-prompt with the validation error appended
  (self-correction, max 2 retries);
  if (still invalid after 2 retries?) then (yes)
    :raise "Failed to generate valid artifact schema";
    stop
  endif
endif
:fan out the single validated object as five SSE events —
JobDescription (40%), EvaluationRubric (60%),
InterviewBlueprint (80%), JobPostMetadata (90%),
CandidateDiscoveryProfile (95%);
note right #ffdddd
  GROUND-TRUTH §6.2: `generate_artifact_stream` **ignores its
  `artifact_type` argument** and delegates straight to
  `generate_all_artifacts_async`, so a request to regenerate one
  artifact silently rewrites all five.
end note

|Background Worker|
while (more SSE events?) is (yes)
  :UpdateSessionProgress / UpsertStage / AddLog;
  :AddMetric input_tokens, output_tokens, cost_usd;
  :SaveArtifactAsync(requirementId, artifactType, jsonData);
endwhile (no)

|PostgreSQL|
:RequirementArtifact / EvaluationRubric /
InterviewBlueprint rows; session Completed;

|Next.js Client|
:SSE events rendered live, then [DONE];

|Organization Member|
:review the artifacts, then publish;

|Next.js Client|
:POST /api/v1/hiring-requirements/{id}/publish;

|Core API|
:PublishAsync — freeze the artifact set;

|PostgreSQL|
:INSERT RequirementSnapshot + ArtifactSnapshots
(a JobDescription snapshot is synthesised if absent);

|Organization Member|
:create the vacancy from the requirement;

|Next.js Client|
:POST /api/v1/job-vacancies/requirement/{id}/create-draft;
:PUT  /api/v1/job-postings/{id};
:POST /api/v1/job-postings/{id}/publish;

|Core API|
:validate and publish the posting;

|PostgreSQL|
:JobVacancy linked to the RequirementSnapshot;

' ---- the candidate-side projection that discovery depends on ----
|Background Worker|
fork
  :CandidateRankingProjectionWorker (every 15 min)
  -> CandidateEvaluationService.EvaluateAndSnapshotCandidateAsync;
  :recalculate trust; consolidate verified repository
  capabilities with self-declared skills;
  |PostgreSQL|
  :upsert CandidateCapabilityProjection, CandidateCapabilities,
  CandidateCapabilityScores, CandidateSearchProfile,
  CandidateEvaluationSnapshot;
  note right #ffdddd
    `candidate_search_profiles.SearchEmbedding` is a `float[]` column
    that **nothing ever writes** — the AI service has no embedding
    module and no vector library is installed (GROUND-TRUTH §6.1).
    The pgvector image runs, but no similarity query exists.
  end note
fork again
  |Background Worker|
  :TalentOutboxBackgroundProcessor (3 s) consumes
  "RepositorySyncTriggered" from `outbox_messages`
  after each repository analysis completes,
  refreshing the same projections;
end fork

|Organization Member|
:"Discover candidates";

|Next.js Client|
:POST /api/v1/hiring-requirements/{id}/candidate-matches/discover;

|Core API|
:INSERT CandidateDiscoveryRun (Pending);
:create AiStreamingSession ("candidate-discovery");
:spawn a detached Task.Run; return { runId, status };

|Background Worker|
:Searching (20%) — status + progress, then Task.Delay(1000);
:Matching (50%) — status + progress, then Task.Delay(1000);
note right #ffdddd
  Both stages are cosmetic: no candidate is searched or matched in
  them. All real work happens once, at Ranking.
end note
:Ranking (80%) -> GetCandidateMatchesAsync;
:for each candidate with a latest assessment,
build UnifiedJobRequirement from the published snapshot
(MustHave weight 1.5, else 1.0; fallback to JobVacancy.Skills)
and call UnifiedMatchingEngine;

|Core API|
:UnifiedMatchingEngine — pure deterministic C#, no AI hop
CapabilityMatch 0.40 · RoleMatch 0.30
· TrustFactor 0.20 · PreferenceMatch 0.10
ConfidenceLevel High >= 80 · Medium >= 50 · else Low;

|PostgreSQL|
:CandidateDiscoveryRun -> Completed
CandidatesFoundCount, RawResultsJson,
MatchQualitySummary "n High Match, n Good Fit, n Potential Fit";

|Organization Member|
:open one candidate for an explainable evaluation;

|Next.js Client|
:GET /api/v1/intelligence/match/{jobVacancyId}/{candidateId};

|Core API|
:ExplainableMatchService.EvaluateMatchAsync;
:DELETE any prior MatchingEvaluation for the pair;
note right
  The previous evaluation is destroyed rather than versioned, so
  matching results are not reproducible after a re-run.
end note
:GetCapabilityIntelligenceAsync(candidateId);
:UnifiedMatchingEngine.EvaluateMatchAsync;

|PostgreSQL|
:INSERT MatchingEvaluation (AggregateScore, ConfidenceLevel);
:INSERT MatchingFactor per factor;
:INSERT MatchingExplanation per assertion
(CapabilityNodeId resolved by Slug or lowered Name,
null when unresolved);

|Next.js Client|
:render score, factor breakdown and explanations;

|Organization Member|
:review evaluation output and decide;
stop

note bottom
  **Not shown because it does not exist.** No stage in this flow parses,
  OCRs or embeds an uploaded CV; no SFIA level or O*NET code influences
  any score (GROUND-TRUTH §6.1). Candidate evidence enters this flow only
  through the repository-analysis and candidate-assessment pipelines.
  Also note that untrusted repository code, commit messages and CV text
  reach Claude prompts with **no injection screening** — `prompt_sanitizer.py`,
  `malicious_repo_detector.py` and `input_boundary.validate_token_count`
  are stubs and none of the three is imported anywhere (§6.5).
end note

@enduml
